what:	Jimarc4random 0.3
where:	https://github.com/aryler/Jimarc4random/
where:	http://www3.bell.net/stwo/software/
who:	Stuart Cassoff <stwo@users.sourceforge.net>
why:	Jim interface to arc4random(3)
when:	Fall 2014
how:	$ ./itzev ?options? && make
how:	$ make test
how:	$ make install
need:	Jim, arc4random(3), POSIX

Jimarc4random should build easily on any POSIX system
that has arc4random(3).

The configuration program is called 'itzev'.
$ ./itzev -help

Use configuration option -bje and Makefile target bje
to build using build-jim-ext.

By default, Jimarc4random will be configured to build
for Jim on OpenBSD.
